WRITING.TITLE: It's okay to not be okay
WRITING.TEXT: I used to think that feeling sad or mad or depressed or any other emotion one would consider "negative" was a bad thing. I always felt that by allowing yourself to feel that way after someone hurt you, it was giving them the upper hand and that drove me crazy so I would try my hardest to smile and just skip right to the part where I'm "over" the situation but someone just told me that there's no such thing as a negative emotion. It's okay to feel pain after someone hurt you. It's okay to cry and be mad and feel depressed as long as you don't let it consume you. I guess what that all means is it's okay to not be okay.

Acoustic demos have a scratchy sound and were just recorded by a simple recorder with Taylor and her guitar/piano. Studio songs are songs that were recorded for Taylor Swift/ Fearless and were cut for one reason or another. For example, Dark Blue Tennessee was meant to go in Fearless but was cut in favor of White Horse Volume 2 was a studio acoustic album that Taylor went door to door hanging out before her fame. Demos are songs that have been finalized and released but these versions are their earliest stages and have gone through lyric/ instrument changes

For instance, the song #8220;Tell Me #8221; was a song that was meant to be included in either Taylor Swift or Fearless and was recorded and finalized but was cut from the final album. It #8217;s a song about lack of communication at the end of a relationship and I consider it one of the best songs she #8217;s ever written. The chorus goes: #8220;Could ya tell me, what did I do? Because it can #8217;t be we #8217;re already through. Did you sell me out for a fool after you held me? Is that just what you do? #8221; The song trade is a circulation of unreleased songs for diehard fans to enjoy. You obtain a song and trade it so another song trader for one you don #8217;t have but leaking a song to an entire community is frowned upon.
